    },
    {
      "end": 132.67999267578125,
      "text": "I hate that you know you want to run, you want to run But if you stay here trusting someone, someone You will find that we all run, around the bend The circle's wisdom becomes your friend",
      "start": 111.68000030517578
    },
    {
      "end": 153.1999969482422,
      "text": "Oh, stop running if you don't want it to be Dark highway, dark stars, dark heart Every time I think it's a dark part Oh, do I remember life?",
      "start": 133.83999633789062
    },
    {
      "end": 173.33999633789062,
      "text": "Oh, the people that I love from The hearts from up above, the ones lost beyond us I know it's something I should ache for Be there, ache for me",
      "start": 153.1999969482422
    },
    {
      "end": 195.22000122070312,
      "text": "A good memory in the last that I'll see of you I hope you don't run back to me, you're far away I hope you're running from, from me and you And the thoughts of all that we could have",
      "start": 173.33999633789062
    },
    {
      "end": 214.22000122070312,
      "text": "Dumb now we're dying inside Now we're all just trying to find a why For why we're here, to mold our lives in the dark Just keep running till there's no time left, there's no time left, there's no time left",
      "start": 195.22000122070312
    },
    {
      "end": 238.77999877929688,
      "text": "Then you look back, regret homing in And the world all lies in your face With fake superstitious, fake you Fake ease, no why, nobody heals Just a test of everything inside of you If you don't know you, stop running from you",
      "start": 215.44000244140625
    },
    {
      "end": 248.36000061035156,
      "text": "Hey, if it was you, if it was me, if it was you Even if you don't know if it was you If it was you, me or me I bet you, I bet you, I mean it's the same thing as I",
      "start": 239.5
    },
    {
      "end": 253.60000610351562,
      "text": "Water, no, no, no, no, no",
